Pumpkin now has frog butt! 
Last week I noticed an infection on the tip of her tail and in order to prevent it from spreading and possibly making her very sick (or worse), I decided to help her drop her tail naturally.
Crested Geckos, among other lizards, have the ability to drop their tails as a defense mechanism, known as autotomy. Unlike other geckos however, cresties can't grow them back.
This does not harm the gecko, and Pumpkin is recovering nicely.
Most people prefer their geckos with tails, but I think tail-less geckos are adorable, don't you agree?

As this is Gingy's first breeding season, these scenarios are not uncommon.
